<div class="row">
    <div class="small-12 columns">
        <h3 class="subheader">Building Operational Data Stores (ODS)</h3>
        <div class="row"  data-equalizer>
            <div class="small-12 medium-6 large-6 columns" data-equalizer-watch>
                <div class="panel radius" data-equalizer-watch>
                    <h5><strong>Scenario</strong></h5>
                    <p>
                        An integrated data repository addresses a specific business area and provides complete and up-to-date information that can be used by business users and BI applications. This is stored in a relational database and receives updates from a dedicated set of programs, ETL or EAI tools. Given that the business need is ensured by an operational data store, it requires timely updates.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="small-12 medium-6 large-6 columns" data-equalizer-watch>
                <div class="panel radius callout" data-equalizer-watch>
                    <h5><strong>Why ARiiP?</strong></h5>
                    <p>
                        ARiiP provides an efficient mechanism to keep an ODS updated by identifying and delivering the changes to the ETL or EAI tool on a continuous basis, rather than periodically querying the entire database for changes. In addition, ARiiP can push changes in near real time, in order to support ODS applications that have very low latency requirements.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
