                    <h5><strong>Scenario</strong></h5>
                    <p>
                       Dashboards provide managers with selected metrics (KPIs), that measure the performance of various business operations. Metrics that are not updated frequently, may mean that managers might become aware of a business problem too late.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="small-12 medium-6 large-6 columns" data-equalizer-watch>
                <div class="panel radius callout" data-equalizer-watch>
                    <h5><strong>Why ARiiP?</strong></h5>
                    <p>
                        ARiiP provides a method of identifying changes that occur to different data sources and that influence the measurement of a specific KPI. For example, an integration can come with data triggers that can process data changes, in a given order, and calculate new values of a specific KPI in a very short time period. This would provide better and timely information to the business user, resulting in much faster and more effective response to changing business conditions.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
